		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Uh... no...! These chips provide extra audio, and are not by any means compatible with the NES CPU. And like I just said, the 2A03 is the CPU, it's responsible for executing the programs, if you get rid of it your NES is dead.

		

		</td>
